From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kanaka Raju Nayana <kanaka.raju.nayana@intel.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 15:00:19 +0530
Subject: drm/xe: detect drm_file.client_id via m4 and guard scheduler
 client_id

On 5.15, struct drm_file does not provide client_id, but Xe scheduler
job paths may pass this value to drm_sched_job_init(), causing build breaks:
struct drm_file has no member named client_id.

Add an m4 probe (AC_DRM_FILE_CLIENT_ID_NOT_PRESENT) and guard the Xe callsites
with BPM_DRM_FILE_CLIENT_ID_NOT_PRESENT: pass 0 when the field is absent,
otherwise pass q->xef->drm->client_id.

This avoids version-based checks and keeps 5.15 backport compatibility without
backporting DRM core drm_file structural changes.

Signed-off-by: Kanaka Raju Nayana <kanaka.raju.nayana@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_sched_job.c     | 4 ++++
 drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_tlb_inval_job.c | 4 ++++
 2 files changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_sched_job.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_sched_job.c
index c69fdc9..58f68a0 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_sched_job.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_sched_job.c
@@ -113,8 +113,12 @@ struct xe_sched_job *xe_sched_job_create(struct xe_exec_queue *q,
 	kref_init(&job->refcount);
 	xe_exec_queue_get(job->q);
 
+#ifdef BPM_DRM_FILE_CLIENT_ID_NOT_PRESENT
+	err = drm_sched_job_init(&job->drm, q->entity, 1, NULL, 0);
+#else
 	err = drm_sched_job_init(&job->drm, q->entity, 1, NULL,
 				 q->xef ? q->xef->drm->client_id : 0);
+#endif
 	if (err)
 		goto err_free;
 
diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_tlb_inval_job.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_tlb_inval_job.c
index 1ae0dec..4011d1d 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_tlb_inval_job.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_tlb_inval_job.c
@@ -120,8 +120,12 @@ xe_tlb_inval_job_create(struct xe_exec_queue *q, struct xe_tlb_inval *tlb_inval,
 	}
 	job->fence = &ifence->base;
 
+#ifdef BPM_DRM_FILE_CLIENT_ID_NOT_PRESENT
+	err = drm_sched_job_init(&job->dep.drm, entity, 1, NULL, 0);
+#else
 	err = drm_sched_job_init(&job->dep.drm, entity, 1, NULL,
 				 q->xef ? q->xef->drm->client_id : 0);
+#endif
 	if (err)
 		goto err_fence;
 
